<subSubSection id="C33F6520EE0DFFCDFCCAFC5BFA915071" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9A36ABEE0DFFCDFCCAFC5BFCC456F1" blockId="4.[810,1456,918,1327]" box="[813,878,918,944]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">NOTE</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9A36ABEE0DFFCDFCCAFC78FA915071" blockId="4.[810,1456,918,1327]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">
According to 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0DFFCDFC51FC78FBEC5690" author="BROWICZ K." box="[950,1094,949,975]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" pagination="32" refId="ref4539" refString="BROWICZ K. 1972. - Cotoneaster Medik., in DAVIS P. H. (ed.), Flora of Turkey. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh 4: L 2 g-L 32." type="journal article" year="1972">Browicz 1972</bibRefCitation>
, this species which is distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0DFFCDFCCCFC18FC2F56B0" box="[811,901,981,1007]" name="Armenia" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Armenia</collectingCountry>
and northeast 
<collectingCountry id="F332763BEE0DFFCDFBFEFC18FBC856B0" box="[1049,1122,981,1007]" name="Turkey" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, was observed among herbarium specimens at HKS (
<figureCitation id="131E2A2EEE0DFFCDFBE4FC38FBFD5150" box="[1027,1111,1013,1039]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[153,164,2008,2025]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[226,1360,215,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Cotoneaster transcaucasicus Pojark.: A, habit;B, leaves and fruits.Collection number:Maroofi &amp; Naseri 6520 (HKS);determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573926" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573926/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0DFFCDFB8DFC38FA885150" box="[1130,1314,1013,1039]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="transcaucasicus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0DFFCDFB8DFC38FA885150" box="[1130,1314,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. transcaucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the closest relative of 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0DFFCDFC73FBD8FAAE5170" authority="Fisch. &amp; C. A. Mey." authorityName="Fisch. &amp; C. A. Mey." box="[916,1284,1045,1071]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nummularius">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0DFFCDFC73FBD8FB905170" box="[916,1082,1045,1071]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. nummularius</emphasis>
Fisch.&amp; C.A.Mey.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB44B5AEE0DFFCDFAF7FBD8FA0A5170" author="BROWICZ K." box="[1296,1440,1045,1071]" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" pagination="32" refId="ref4539" refString="BROWICZ K. 1972. - Cotoneaster Medik., in DAVIS P. H. (ed.), Flora of Turkey. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh 4: L 2 g-L 32." type="journal article" year="1972">Browicz 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Generally, these species have some similarities in features of leaves (size) fruit color (red), calyx orientation, indumentum of all parts except in sepals. On the other hand, there are a few remarkable differences between these species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C254D28EE0DFFCDFB1BFB58FA0751F1" box="[1276,1453,1173,1199]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Cotoneaster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="4" pageNumber="143" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="transcaucasicus">
<emphasis id="B951EAB9EE0DFFCDFB1BFB58FA0751F1" box="[1276,1453,1173,1199]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">C. transcaucasicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by obovate leaves with cuneate base and widely rounded-emarginate apex (
<figureCitation id="131E2A2EEE0DFFCDFBA9FB19FB3451B0" box="[1102,1182,1236,1263]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="5.[153,164,2008,2025]" captionTargetId="figure-19@5.[226,1360,215,1805]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIG. 2. — Cotoneaster transcaucasicus Pojark.: A, habit;B, leaves and fruits.Collection number:Maroofi &amp; Naseri 6520 (HKS);determined by Raei Niaki &amp; Attar." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6573926" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6573926/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="143">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
